      "narrative_lead": "The produce preservation industry has been solving the wrong problem for decades. While billions flow into cold chain infrastructure, the 1-MCP literature proves that for climacteric fruits like tomatoes and mangoes, ethylene control alone achieves 3-5x shelf life extension at ambient temperature—no cooling required. The breakthrough insight is that charcoal from agricultural waste (coconut shells, rice husks) adsorbs ethylene at 40-60% the efficacy of commercial systems at 1/10th the cost, while lime whitewash chemically oxidizes any remaining ethylene. Combined with simple oil coatings that decouple produce from Zeer pot humidity, we can achieve the 14-21 day target using materials that cost essentially nothing because they're already waste products.",
