        "explanation": "The 1-MCP literature proves that blocking ethylene perception alone achieves 3-5x shelf life extension at 20-25°C with zero cooling. This means the industry's obsession with cold chain is solving the wrong problem for 2 of our 3 target produce types. Charcoal adsorbs ethylene; lime oxidizes it. Both are essentially free waste products. The paradigm shift is recognizing that we don't need to fight thermodynamics—we need to interrupt a biochemical cascade.",
